        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I'm having an odd issue with _forward and ContextSwitch, which looks like it could be a ZF bug.\nI'm switching the output format using the ContextSwitch helper in my controller's init() method, which all works fine.\nHowever, if an action of this controller forwards to another controller's action, the content-type header is set, layout rendering is disabled, but the switched view script (in this case, WML) is not used.\nThis is resulting in a page being sent with a WML header, but the XHTML view script (minus the layout).\nIt seems to be inconsistent... I can't reproduce it on my machine, but on the test servers it happens every time."
        },
